From: Sai Lakshmi Teja Vanka <SaiLakshmiTeja.Vanka@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Apr 2026 03:28:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Export PROJECT_VERSION to fix version detection

The rabbitmq build system resolves PROJECT_VERSION through a chain:
Makefile -> rabbitmq-components.mk -> git-revisions.txt/git-describe.
Some sub-makefiles (e.g. deps/rabbit_common/mk/rabbitmq-components.hexpm.mk)
run in subdirectories without git-revisions.txt or a git repo, causing
PROJECT_VERSION to fall back to 0.0.0.

Export PROJECT_VERSION from debian/rules using the version already
extracted from debian/changelog, so it propagates to all makefiles
via the environment.

---
 debian/rules | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
index 1234567..abcdefg 100755
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -4,6 +4,7 @@
 DEB_DESTDIR=debian/rabbitmq-server
 VERSION = $(shell dpkg-parsechangelog -SVersion | sed -e 's/^[[:digit:]]*://' -e 's/[-].*//' -e 's/~/.0/' -e 's/+dfsg1//' | head -n 1)
 
+export PROJECT_VERSION = $(VERSION)
 export LC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8
 export LANG=en_US.UTF-8
 
